"We rise by lifting others" Robert Ingersoll Important update 3 Feb 2019Thank you to everyone who has helped to promote, contribute and be a part of this campaign. My original campaign was launched  in October 2018 but had a campaign time limit of 60 days (like all other campaigns). As I wanted this campaign to last for three months, the only way around this was to create the second part of this campaign (all aspects are the same) to allow this campaign to stay alive. You can view the original campaign and all backers at the link above. Ongoing efforts will be saved and highlighted here. Am sorry for the inconvenience but these are the limitations of this platform. All funds will go to Cancer Research Malaysia. Who is Rowena Morais? Hi there, I am Rowena Morais. Wife, mom of three and at time of writing, 46 years old. An editor and writer based in Kuala Lumpur, who specialises in learning, communication and content. I run, lift weights and practise taekwondo. Diagnosed with Stage 2 breast cancer in June 2018, I am blown away by how quickly my life has shifted, both for me and those around me.I am making sense as best I can of what has happened. I believe in taking action, finding my way around a problem and moving forward. The reason I'm sharing what I learn along the way is because I hope that it may be of use to those on similar journeys. What is this charity campaign for?Let's start with some simple worldwide statistics:
18.1 million new cancer cases and 9.1 million deaths due to cancer in 2018 for both sexes, all ages  according to the International Agency for Research on cancer;
2.1 million new breast cancer cases and 676 thousand deaths due to breast cancer in 2018;
Breast cancer is the most common cancer in the overwhelming majority of countries around the world, and 75% of deaths occur in low and middle-income countries.
As you can see, cancer is a problem that's been around for some time now and affects a great many people -  man, woman, old and young.Infographic   source: The EconomistI am raising money for cancer research so that the vital work that needs to continue into cures, new breakthroughs, experimental drugs and innovative therapies may continue. As I am in Malaysia and getting treatment locally, I would like to direct the funds raised to a local non-profit organisation. Who benefits from this charity campaign?The beneficiary of this campaign is Cancer Research Malaysia, an independent and non-profit cancer research organisation based in Malaysia which is funded entirely by donations, research grants and the public. Cancer Research Malaysia conducts research into niche cancers often found in the Asian population. What will you help achieve?Your contribution, financial or otherwise, will help direct even more awareness, continued education and research into cancer as a whole.We need to press for continued vigilance in how we actively manage our health because this is something we need to take charge of. What are the goals of Cancer Research Malaysia?
Improving the survival rates of Asian cancer patients, focusing on neglected areas of research;
Empowering Asians to have the proper screening and treatment;
Improving survival rates by being more accessible, focusing on providing existing cures to patients rather than sit on inaction and potentially losing lives;
Making affordable and timely treatments by repurposing drugs, acknowledging the reality that developing new cures are costly and risky;
Putting Malaysia in the global spotlight for cancer research by collaborating with top scientists around the world, and working to nurture the next generation of Malaysian cancer researchers.
 Why am I doing this and why does this matter?I want to take positive, proactive action to deal with cancer that goes beyond my individual experience. I'm hoping that the work I do to shine a light on this and the collective effort of many through donations, social media and discussion, will help drive a greater good that can only be achieved by a collective spirit and not just the one individual.This makes it wider than the one experience.  This helps me feel like I am contributing to something bigger than myself, and ultimately, it will make a difference and be impactful to many others.This matters because this is not just my story – it is the story of literally millions of people around the world, people like you and me and their families. This matters because we all can take action to make a difference, in whatever capacity we wish.It matters because this is both personal and universal. What do I need from you?If my story resonates, I urge you to make a donation of any amount towards this cause. Give as you can, give what you will.I also urge you to spread the word through social media or any other means because you can and the work you do will make a difference. How much?A special note to say any amount will do.While I appreciate the unstinting generosity of the backers who have contributed in the early stages of this campaign, I want to stress that every single dollar counts. So feel free to donate even USD1, USD5 or USD10 or any amount you feel comfortable and able to give. What matters is your involvement, contribution and amplification of this message to help carry this campaign through. What do you get from this?An opportunity to be part of something bigger than yourself and which will have tremendous meaning to those impacted by this disease. How long is this campaign?6 months from October 2018 – March 2019. On the perk  For those who would like to take me up on my offer of the 30 min skype call, feel free to reach out via email so we can lock in a date/time that suits both. You can email me at hello AT rowenamorais.com. All the ways you can helpDonate money | Amplify this message Risks & ChallengesThe risks and obstacles I face in working to achieve this goal are the following:1. I can't do this alone - I am counting on the growing network I have to raise awareness and money.2. There are many worthy causes out there that justify equal or more weight. Mine is just one more.3. I am currently undergoing chemotherapy treatment myself which means I have to manage my health alongside my work and this campaign.That said, I intend to support this campaign through advocacy, education and awareness. I hope you will join me.  “What you do makes a difference, and you have to decide what kind of difference you want to make.”- Jane Goodall
